(8482, 1, '2017-02-01 15:16:23', '2017-02-01 15:16:23', '[vc_row css=".vc_custom_1474965242775{margin-bottom: 0px !important;}" parallax_background=""][vc_column][vc_column_text]\r\n<h3>Through the Health Management Information Systems, Program Area D (HMIS), METS is Aiming at:-</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li><strong>I</strong>mproving patient <span style="color: #008000;">identification</span>, tracking, service provision and referrals of persons with HIVs along the clinical cascade.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>I</strong>ncrease availability of <span style="color: #993300;">critical <strong>HMIS</strong> tools</span> at health facilities to facilitate <span style="color: #008000;"><strong>data</strong> collection and reporting</span>.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>E</strong>stablish and expand functional electronic HMIS at national, districts and high volume facilities</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>I</strong>mprove <em><strong><span style="color: #008000;">data quality</span></strong></em> and use for <span style="color: #993300;">better planning</span> and decision-making at district and facility levels.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>S</strong>trengthen ordering and reporting of <span style="color: #008000;">ARVs</span> and <span style="color: #008000;">HIV</span> test kits using the web-based ordering system (WAOS).</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>E</strong>stablish a data-sharing platform which pulls data from <em>DATIM</em>, <em>DHIS2</em> and other sources to act as a central repository for <span style="color: #008000;">HIV data</span>.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_single_image image="8483" img_size="600x300" alignment="center" style="vc_box_border" hover_effect="img_reduce_opacity"][vc_custom_heading text="The <strong>projects interventions</strong>" font_container="tag:h2|font_size:30|text_align:left" google_fonts="font_family:Lato%3A100%2C100italic%2C300%2C300italic%2Cregular%2Citalic%2C700%2C700italic%2C900%2C900italic|font_style:300%20light%20regular%3A300%3Anormal" el_class="letterspacing-2"][vc_column_text]\r\n<div class="page" title="Page 5">\r\n<div class="layoutArea">\r\n<div class="column">\r\n\r\nIn 2015, The Ministry of Health approved OpenMRS as an electronic patient records system and indicated the need to expand the system to cater for all the other program areas. With support from CDC, METS in 2015 received support to customize and support the national scale-up of OpenMRS. METS upgraded the existing OpenMRS (Version 1.6.3 to Version 1.11.6 which was rebranded from OpenMRS to UgandaEMR. <a href="http://emrportal.mets.or.ug/" target="_blank">VISIT THE PORTAL</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_custom_heading text="HMIS Tools" font_container="tag:h2|font_size:30|text_align:left" google_fonts="font_family:Lato%3A100%2C100italic%2C300%2C300italic%2Cregular%2Citalic%2C700%2C700italic%2C900%2C900italic|font_style:300%20light%20regular%3A300%3Anormal" el_class="letterspacing-2"][vc_column_text]\r\n<div class="page" title="Page 5">\r\n<div class="layoutArea">\r\n<div class="column">\r\n\r\n<em><strong>METS printed critical HMIS tools</strong></em> including Registers, Forms and Clients Cards for the entire country. All (100%) of the 44 critical HMIS tools were printed and majority distributed through Implementing Partners, districts and to the health facilities for further knowledge generation and sharing.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_single_image image="7735" img_size="medium" alignment="center" style="vc_box_shadow_circle" onclick="zoom" hover_effect="img_reduce_opacity"][vc_custom_heading text="Capacity Building" font_container="tag:h2|font_size:30|text_align:left" google_fonts="font_family:Lato%3A100%2C100italic%2C300%2C300italic%2Cregular%2Citalic%2C700%2C700italic%2C900%2C900italic|font_style:300%20light%20regular%3A300%3Anormal" el_class="letterspacing-2"][vc_column_text]\r\n<div class="page" title="Page 5">\r\n<div class="layoutArea">\r\n<div class="column">\r\n\r\nFor sustainability as far as capacity building is concerned, METS in collaboration with the Ministry of Health, Division of Health Information, <a href="http://www.who.int/" target="_blank">WHO</a> and <a href="https://www.cdc.gov/" target="_blank">CDC</a> organized the first ever National OpenMRS Trainer of Trainers in Mbarara to build capacity countrywide. The workshop provided participants with practical hands on training on the updated <a href="http://emrportal.mets.or.ug/" target="_blank">UgandaEMR</a> system. The training that targeted IT and M&amp;E staff from various CDC and USAID supported Implementing Partners (IPs). The 120 participants that relate with the use of OpenMRS across the country.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_custom_heading text="Strategic <strong>Planning Workshops</strong>" font_container="tag:h2|font_size:30|text_align:left" google_fonts="font_family:Lato%3A100%2C100italic%2C300%2C300italic%2Cregular%2Citalic%2C700%2C700italic%2C900%2C900italic|font_style:300%20light%20regular%3A300%3Anormal" el_class="letterspacing-2"][vc_column_text]\r\n<div class="page" title="Page 5">\r\n<div class="layoutArea">\r\n<div class="column">\r\n\r\n<strong>DHIS2 Technical Support to Ministry of Health:</strong> METS supported the Ministry of Health to conduct two eHMIS orientation trainings for the National Level Programs and Armed forces (police, Army and Prisons). To maintain a reliable national eHMIS system, the project further supported the Ministry of Health to customize the national DHIS2. Missing data validation rules and indicators for the different program areas including TB, and Malaria, were identified and integrated into the national DHIS2 during the quarter.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="layoutArea">\r\n<div class="column">\r\n\r\n<strong>EOC-MOH support:</strong> METS supported the Emergency Operation Centre (EOC) with eMTCT Option B+ and Retention Reporting. The project supported the MoH to schedule weekly presentations and sent out reminders for reporting, and presentations to the different stakeholders. The <a href="http://dashboard.mets.or.ug" target="_blank">Option B+ report platform</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="layoutArea">\r\n<div class="column">\r\n\r\n<strong>HIV Situation Room:</strong> Together with the Ministry of Health, the Division of Health Information, participated in a study tour on the Situation Room in Nairobi. The Situation Room provides a platform for managers to have access to data from different data sources to make accurate decisions a concept that METS plans to support the Ministry of Health in. <a href="http://mets.or.ug">METS</a> is now working out a concepts to have this implemented in Uganda.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="column"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_custom_heading text="<strong>Innovations</strong>" font_container="tag:h2|font_size:30|text_align:left" google_fonts="font_family:Lato%3A100%2C100italic%2C300%2C300italic%2Cregular%2Citalic%2C700%2C700italic%2C900%2C900italic|font_style:300%20light%20regular%3A300%3Anormal" el_class="letterspacing-2"][vc_column_text]\r\n<div class="page" title="Page 5">\r\n<div class="layoutArea">\r\n<div class="column">\r\n\r\n<strong>These @METS</strong> include Health Informatics Mapper known as the <em><strong>HiMap</strong></em>. This is an eHealth strategic information application that can be used to capture the GIS coordinates for the District Health Offices and Health Facilities across the country. The application will also enable the user to access the District Health Offices and Health Facilities across the country.\r\n<div class="page" title="Page 5">\r\n<div class="layoutArea">\r\n<div class="column">\r\n\r\n<strong>The Strategic Information Mobile Application and Option B+ Dashboard</strong>\r\n\r\nThis is a mobile based application that was developed by METS for the Ministry of Health to monitor the Elimination of Mother To Child Transmission (<em><strong>eMTCT</strong></em>) of HIV program.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="layoutArea"></div>\r\n<div class="layoutArea"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_custom_heading text="<strong>Publications</strong> | <i>Articles, Papers &amp; Bulletin</i>" font_container="tag:h2|font_size:30|text_align:left" google_fonts="font_family:Lato%3A100%2C100italic%2C300%2C300italic%2Cregular%2Citalic%2C700%2C700italic%2C900%2C900italic|font_style:300%20light%20regular%3A300%3Anormal" el_class="letterspacing-2"][vc_column_text el_class="publication"]\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B4jwP0ShI6fCSmtEdl90ckpPMmdNOTRJaVJtQkRPSjVNTC0w"> CypherHealth Uganda: An automated health facility coding and inventory system for Uganda | </a><em>by Stephen Ocaya, Eric Munyambabazi, and Jonathan Mpango.</em></li>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B4jwP0ShI6fCaURQZzRfaC1Gb3dQMDFNN0dPeWxRZ3ZHdnZJ">eHealth Bulletin Issue 2 - September 2016</a> |<em>Contributor - Mr. Jonathan Mpango &amp; Samuel Lubwama – Makerere University School of Public </em><em>Health, METS Program</em></li>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B4jwP0ShI6fCT2VEVWlPT042YjRkOXBrNXU5WUtxel8yaHNv">ROLLOUT OF PATIENTS ELECTRONIC MANAGEMENT RECORDS SYSTEM IN UGANDA (UGANDAEMR)</a> | <em>Author: Mwotasubi Isaac, Ocaya Stephen, Charity Kyomugasho, Evelyn Akello, </em>William Bazeyo.</li>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B4jwP0ShI6fCYVRveVBhNUR4aTlpS3pCSmxOeUxpZjhoMkFz">The Use of Dashboards in Performance Management for Public Health Interventions in Uganda: A Case of Option B+ Surveillance</a> | <em>by Kaye Milton. Makerere University School of Public Health, METS Program.</em></li>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B4jwP0ShI6fCU2thc1ZROW1JdDRfNE5UbDVqbGhMbXJQbWZB">Empowering girls and reducing HIV infections by the DREAMS Program</a> | <em>by Daisy Shirley Kusiima</em></li>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B4jwP0ShI6fCdC1CWHlITno4aElzNWhoOEcwSm5BY2lXdjE0">e-Health Bulletin Issue 1 - April 2016</a> | <em>by By Mr. Moses Bagyendera, WHO-Uganda | Writers  Jonathan Mpango</em></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p class="page" title="Page 5"><em> </em></p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Health Management Information Systems', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'health-management-information-systems', '', '', '2017-03-23 14:42:49', '2017-03-23 14:42:49', '', 0, 'http://mets.or.ug/?page_id=8482', 0, 'page', '', 0),
