(8902, 2, '2017-05-18 07:41:57', '2017-05-18 07:41:57', 'The Monitoring and Evaluation Technical Support (METS) Program through the DLP project runs a medium term fellowship in Governance, Leadership and Management (GLM) for district health managers. The project will conduct the first face to face sessions for the 2nd cohort of fellows', 'GLM FELLOWS TRAINING', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'glm-fellows-training', '', '', '2017-05-18 07:41:57', '2017-05-18 07:41:57', '', 0, 'http://mets.or.ug/?post_type=ajde_events&#038;p=8902', 0, 'ajde_events', '', 0),
(8903, 2, '2017-05-18 07:58:40', '2017-05-18 07:58:40', 'Monitoring and Evaluation Technical Support (METS) program was mandated by CDC to provide technical support in setting up a monitoring and evaluation system for the Partner Health Services (PHS) pilot program in Kiboga and Rakai. Against this background, the stakeholders (MOH, CDC and collaborating IPs) have scheduled a field monitoring visit to the two pilot districts the week of 5-9 June 2017', 'District monitoring visits to support implementation of partner health  services', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'district-monitoring-visits-to-support-implementation-of-partner-health-services', '', '', '2017-06-01 14:06:59', '2017-06-01 14:06:59', '', 0, 'http://mets.or.ug/?post_type=ajde_events&#038;p=8903', 0, 'ajde_events', '', 0),
(8904, 2, '2017-05-18 08:54:31', '2017-05-18 08:54:31', 'The monitoring and Evaluation Technical Support (METS) program through the DLP component supports enhancement of district coordination of the decentralized HIV response. This mandate is fulfilled in close collaboration with district based IPs. Against this background, METS has received an invitation from the Infectious Disease Institute (IDI) to attend the regional review meetings for districts in West Nile.', 'Regional Review Meetings', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'regional-review-meetings', '', '', '2017-05-18 08:54:31', '2017-05-18 08:54:31', '', 0, 'http://mets.or.ug/?post_type=ajde_events&#038;p=8904', 0, 'ajde_events', '', 0),
(8906, 2, '2017-05-18 09:29:16', '2017-05-18 09:29:16', 'A set of monitoring tools for Viral Load were developed including the Non suppressed Register, Viral Load reporting addendum and the Non suppressed tally sheet to be used to track clients who are non-suppressed. A Training of Trainers was done and this team working with the Implementing Partners went out and piloted the developed data collection tools at selected high volume sites in the partner supported sites. The result of which was updating of the data collection tools, as well as generation of the VL addendum per facility mentored-this was captured into the DHIS2.', 'Mentorship on the viral load monitoring tools', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'mentorship-on-the-viral-load-monitoring-tools', '', '', '2017-05-18 11:59:34', '2017-05-18 11:59:34', '', 0, 'http://mets.or.ug/?post_type=ajde_events&#038;p=8906', 0, 'ajde_events', '', 0),
(8907, 2, '2017-05-18 12:31:29', '2017-05-18 12:31:29', 'METS is mandated to provide above site support to CDC-supported Implementing Partners (IPs) and districts. Provision of above site support involves strengthening district systems to support health service delivery as well as supporting Ministry of Health and IPs to achieve their mandate. CDC Uganda has scheduled SIMS assessment visits', 'Above Site (District) SIMS assessment', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'above-site-district-sims-assessment', '', '', '2017-05-18 12:31:29', '2017-05-18 12:31:29', '', 0, 'http://mets.or.ug/?post_type=ajde_events&#038;p=8907', 0, 'ajde_events', '', 0),
