(8973, 2, '2017-06-01 13:57:01', '2017-06-01 13:57:01', 'An increasing number of people living with HIV are accessing ART. Despite this increasing number, Uganda has often severely suffered from continuous lack of ARVs drugs. Health facilities are either completely out of stock, understocked or overstocked of ARV drugs. To efficiently monitor the stock status of the antiretroviral (ARVs) drugs, a functional real-time ARV stock status monitoring dashboard is required.\r\n\r\nMonitoring and Evaluation Technical Support (METS) Program with support from CDC Uganda has developed an ARV stock status reporting system based on DHIS2 and utilizes the SMS platform for stock reporting. There will be two consecutive trainings in West Nile (Arua) and Western - Rwenzori Regions (Kabarole) districts on the said dashboard.', 'Pilot of Real-time ARV Stock Status Monitoring Dashboard', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'pilot-of-real-time-arv-stock-status-monitoring-dashboard-2', '', '', '2017-06-01 14:01:19', '2017-06-01 14:01:19', '', 0, 'http://mets.or.ug/?post_type=ajde_events&#038;p=8973', 0, 'ajde_events', '', 0),
(8974, 2, '2017-06-01 14:13:24', '2017-06-01 14:13:24', 'Monitoring and Evaluation Technical Support (METS) program was mandated by CDC to provide technical support in setting up a monitoring and evaluation system for the Partner Health Services (PHS) pilot program in Kiboga and Rakai. Against this background, the stakeholders (MOH, CDC and collaborating IPs) have scheduled a field monitoring visit to the two pilot districts the week of 5-9 June 2017', 'District monitoring visits to support implementation of Partner Health Services', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'district-monitoring-visits-to-support-implementation-of-partner-health-services-2', '', '', '2017-06-01 14:13:24', '2017-06-01 14:13:24', '', 0, 'http://mets.or.ug/?post_type=ajde_events&#038;p=8974', 0, 'ajde_events', '', 0),
(8975, 2, '2017-06-01 14:18:26', '2017-06-01 14:18:26', 'M&amp;E program area plans to conduct a joint on-site mentorship and quality assessments at 60 CDC-supported VMMC sites. The sites include the newly identified sites in COP16 and those found with suboptimal quality VMMC services during the previous assessment conducted in January 2017. In collaboration with the supporting IPs and MoH, this activity is intended to; i) assess the quality of VMMC services offered at each site using the MOH Quality assessment tool, ii) identify VMMC service quality gaps and develop action plans for continuous quality improvement, iii) asses the adaptation of the new MoH VMMC- TT vaccination guidance, iv) VMMC data validation for the period January-March 2017.\r\n\r\nA total of six teams have been formed to conduct the exercise. Each team will visit 10 sites over a 10 day period from June 5-17 2017. Each team is expected to visit, mentor and assess one VMMC site per day.', 'VMMC service quality assessment and mentorship', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'vmmc-service-quality-assessment-and-mentorship', '', '', '2017-06-01 14:18:26', '2017-06-01 14:18:26', '', 0, 'http://mets.or.ug/?post_type=ajde_events&#038;p=8975', 0, 'ajde_events', '', 0),
